parameters:
"Welcome back, and you brought Suelle with you today, I
see."

"Yes, we ran into each other in the cave by chance. And
here, Selphie, I've finished the scheduled monster
subjugation."

Selphie receives something like a tube from Tina and when
she puts power into it, characters appear in the air.

This tube is also a piece of equipment, and it keeps a
detailed record of the subjugation.

"Yes, I've confirmed it. This is the paper for the reward.
As usual, you can cash it in at the exchange office."
Suelle takes another look at Selphie.

Unlike Tina, she gives off the impression of a tidy and
mature woman.

Selphie is an expert gunner and one of the hero members,
Lucent.

After the demon lord's subjugation, she belonged to an
organization called the Legal Affairs Department, where she
cracks down on villains, maintains public order against
disruptive monsters, and brokers special requests run by
nobles.
But what's even more impressive are her huge breasts.

Those bombshell boobs will eventually be mine to fondle and
knead as much as I want.

"No, maybe I should just dive in and nibble on them right
now..."

"Enough!! Tina Onee-san, stop imitating my voice from behind
and speaking my inner thoughts!!"

"Eh, but... you're always looking at Selphie's boobs, aren't
you?"

"No, no, that's a misunderstanding!! Sure, they might catch
my eye from time to time but..."

Realizing his slip of the tongue, Suelle shifts his gaze to
Selphie with an awkward expression.

"(The face she shows when I accidentally touch her breasts
or when I mistakenly enter the bath she's in)"
(That's the face known as, 'I'll pretend I didn't know.')

"I had noticed you glancing my way from time to time. I
thought we might need to have a talk about it."

"Also, if you fondle my breasts now, you might be seen by
another member of Lucent who has just returned after a long
time."

Upon hearing Selphie's words, Suelle recalls another member
of Lucent besides Tina and Selphie.
"Does that mean... Rise has come back?"
"Yes, she's back from her expedition after three months."
"It seems someone is calling for me!!"
"It's been a while, everyone!! Lady Rise has returned!!"

This girl is one of the members of Lucent, her name is Rise.
She is a genius who has mastered skills called spells.

Together with the members gathered here and the hero who
returned to the original world, they defeated the demon lord
as Lucent.

In other words, excluding the returned hero, the demon lord
subjugation members are all gathered here.

But more importantly, I have always wanted to experience
Rise's body. The softness that comes with being a woman.
"Maybe I should just bite into her right now..."

"Enough already!! Tina Onee-san, don't imitate my voice for
the second time!!"
"Rise, it's not like that!! Please believe me!!"
"Suelle, you're still head over heels for me, I see."

"That's not it!! Why are you making such a smug face as if
you've seen through everything!!"

"I'd understand if it were Selphie-san or Tina Onee-san, but
I've never looked at Rise with those eyes, so rest
assured!!"

"Ah, no!! I didn't mean anything deep by it!! In a good
way!!"
"Where is the good in what you just said!!?"

"Hmph, well fine. Suelle. If you want me to forgive you for
disgracing me, then become my slave!!"
"Why do I have to do that!!?"

Laughter spilled from those around, and the closeness of the
Lucent members could be felt in every aspect of this scene.
"But I'm glad to see you're well after such a long time."

"You were on an expedition for three months to take down a
super-sized monster in the neighboring country, right? It
must have been a pretty strong creature. Were you okay?"

"For all his complaints, Suelle was really worried about
you."
"Don't worry. A monster of that level is no match for me."

"It took three months because there was scouting,
preparation, and subjugation of surrounding monsters
involved, which delayed things."
With that, Rise showed off her equipment.

"My equipment is a bit special, so the equipment smiths over
there had a hard time with it."

Spellcasters, unlike swordsmen or shield bearers, use skills
to produce fire or water, making adjustments significantly
more difficult.

Especially for equipment that can withstand the highest
levels, even for skilled equipment smiths, adjustments can
be quite challenging.

"I once again realized how amazing Suelle is for being able
to adjust such equipment with ease."
"I'm still far from being as good as everyone else."
"Hmph, I feel like it's been a while since I've heard that."

"But, I am praising you!! Be happy about it, and show your
gratitude by kneeling and licking my feet!!"

As the heroes gathered for the first time in a while, Tina
made a suggestion.

"Since we're all together for the first time in a while, why
don't we go out for drinks afterwards?"

She puffed out her chest, showing the paper with today's
reward money, offering to treat them. It was a substantial
amount.

Nolz and Rise nodded at her words. However, Selphie shook
her head apologetically at Tina's suggestion.

"I'd really like to, but I have to sort out the aftermath of
the recent incident."

"Ah, that thing. It does seem like there's still a lot to
deal with."
"Ah, right. Rise just got back, so she wouldn't know."
"Hmph, Hmph!! I-I know about it too!!"
"Why are you getting competitive about this!!?"

"Well, actually, not too long ago we apprehended a large-
scale human trafficking organization. There's still some
transport and paperwork that needs to be sorted out."

"It was amazing, you know? Selphie almost single-handedly
took down a big organization."
"Heh, I didn't know something like that happened."

Rise smiled softly, realizing that her companions had been
active and successful even in her absence.

"And the top person in that human trafficking ring was a
woman. The world is full of surprises."
At Tina's words, Suelle looked at the three of them.

(Hmm, looking at the three of them, I don't find it strange
at all that the top was a woman.)

Having several women with overwhelming strength nearby,
Suelle was able to accept the facts smoothly without any
surprise.

"There's also another thing, and I hate to ask you one after
another, but there's something I need Tina's help with."

"Yes, actually there have been several reports lately about
the ecosystem of monsters around this town changing, with
stronger demons occasionally appearing around the town."

"!! That's right, today I was attacked by a monster near the
Eld Cavern!!"
"Rather, the reason I came here today was to report that."

"Monsters have come that far... But thank goodness you're
safe."
"I happened to pass by and took the liberty of subduing it."

"Is that so... Thank you, Tina. It could have been serious
if you hadn't been there."

While everyone else was talking, Rise was glaring at
Suelle's body.

She was probably thinking of using a healing spell if she
found even a small wound.

At the beginning of their travels, Suelle was intimidated by
Rise's stern gaze, but in reality, she is a kind girl who
always cares for Suelle, a non-combatant who cannot heal
himself.

"Hehe, so? The reason you've come to me this time is also
related to the changes in the monster ecosystem?"
"Yes, that matter included... First, take a look at this."
Selphie took out a piece of paper.

Upon looking at the paper, it turned out to be a request
form.

"Actually, after investigating the movements of the
monsters, it seems that a new species of monster is involved
in causing them to move."

"It seems likely that this new species is residing in a cave
called the Crié Cavern, which is a little distance from here
and connects this town with the next."

"A new species of monster... So other monsters were driven
away by it and ended up coming close to town?"

"Yes, and it seems that a noble named Maroges is planning to
investigate the monster. That's why the request for an
escort has come to us."
"Ah, I see. So it's for the purpose of naming."

When a new species of monster appears, the right to name it
is granted to the person who captures or subdues it.

Since the name of the discoverer will also be recorded in
the bestiary, it's common for nobles to want to capture or
subdue new species of monsters.

However, nobles do not fight themselves. It's standard
practice to have an escort for inspection, capture, and
subjugation.

"So, to get to the main point of the story, I'd like to
entrust Tina with the escort of Maroges."

Tina is a skilled fighter who was even part of a hero's
party. She is exceptionally strong, standing out from the
others.

Therefore, if there is no urgency, higher-ranked adventurers
usually take on the request first, assess the situation, and
if necessary, Tina is called into action. That's the general
practice.

It was unusual for Tina herself to be requested as an escort
from the start, as is the case this time.

"There's a little problem. Earlier, I was called by Gugukas,
the head of legal affairs, and heard a certain story."

"Gugukas, that's the most important person in the legal
department, right?"

"For someone like that to call Selphie directly, what
happened?"

And so Selphie began to recount her conversation with
Gugukas to everyone.

Several hours ago, in the office of Chief Legal Officer
Gugukas.
"Hehe, I've been waiting for you, Selphie-chan."

"I'm sorry for being late, I had a lot of things to take
care of."
"So, what was the reason you called for me?"

"Yes, about that... It's regarding the human trafficking
organization you helped us catch the other day."

"We were able to locate and protect the women who were
enslaved based on the roster we found there, but... a little
problem has arisen."

"Actually, among the women we protected, there's someone who
claims she became a slave of her own free will."

"I was surprised too. I used my skills to interrogate her,
and it seems she's speaking from her heart."

"Moreover, upon investigating her background, it turns out
she said goodbye to her surroundings and went to the slave
organization on her own before becoming a slave."

"I felt that was definitely strange, so I had my
subordinates continue the investigation, and it turns out
there was a common factor among these women."

"All of them were women who had taken on a request from a
noble named Maroges."

"I see. So there's a possibility that Maroges, our client
this time, is somehow involved in human trafficking."

"That's why we're asking Tina to take on the escort request
and investigate Maroges at the same time."

"Certainly, if we don't know what the other party will do,
Tina is the best suited for the job."

"Right, Tina Onee-san has that unique skill called Full
Body, after all."

In this world, aside from the normal skills that anyone can
use if they have the aptitude, there are special skills that
are unique to individuals.
Full Body is one such skill, exclusive to Tina.

During the demon lord subjugation era, there were dangerous
moments when she was shot by bullets from manipulated
children in surprise attacks.

However, Tina's ability known as Full Body is a passive
skill that automatically deflects any surprise attack.

"Given that we don't know what the opponent will do, sudden
surprise attacks and powerful traps are certainly
conceivable."

"That's exactly why Tina, with her unique skill Full Body,
is perfect for this mission."

"Hmm, but even so, Full Body won't activate unless it's an
attack I'm not aware of, and when it switches to automatic
defense, my consciousness is interrupted for a moment."

"That momentary delay can be a decisive opening in a fight
against a formidable enemy, so I'd rather not have it
activate too often."

Tina's moment is literally just that—a moment. For example,
someone with as little combat experience as Suelle wouldn't
even be able to perceive it.

"Well, it's not like I often fight opponents of that level
anyway."
"   Understood. I'll take on the job."

"That's a relief. If this matter were just a coincidence, it
would be fine, but it's too perfect to be mere coincidence."

"Considering that the upper echelons of the legal department
are moving, it's almost certain that he's a person of
interest who is practically confirmed to be guilty. Don't
let your guard down, Tina."

"The deadline for this request is three weeks. If by any
chance we don't receive a completion report by then, we'll
start searching the moment the deadline passes."

"To prevent that from happening, I'll make sure to keep in
touch using the communication device and notify you
immediately if anything happens."

"Understood. I'll take care of the acceptance procedure
here. And Tina, take this."
Tina has obtained the \C[2]Nobles' Quarter Pass\C[0].

"With this pass, you can go straight to Maroges' place, so
please go and have a meeting with him."
"   Be especially careful not to arouse any suspicion."
"Then, let's call it a day and disband for now."
